President Obama has declared a major disaster in South Dakota due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred between June 16-24, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The declaration includes funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael L. Parker has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.